rComments: He was a summer school teacher at uwo this summer teaching math 1600. He was just horrible. I had to sit through 3 hours of him regurgitating information from the textbook. His explanations were not clear either. Tbh, you have a lot easier time trying to read the textbook on you own than going to class and listen to him reading the textbook.

I took my first calculus course during a six-week summer session with Professor Mousavi. Given the limitations of a short course, he did a good job of going through lots of examples. His assignments were very difficult, and the exams were difficult, but fair. He cares about student learning, but assumes they are better prepared than they really are

Horrible, just horrible. He did not explain things well. Test questions were not like what was in the textbook, which was how we were supposed to study. He used complicated questions and did not understand why we were all confused.

Doesn't know how to teach.  Useless.  Based his entire teaching on the textbook then tested us on things we never learned or weren't even in the textbook.  Our exam "review" was the homework for the entire course.
